<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idd0f75cd2-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e" identifier="/us/usc/t50/s167g"><num value="167g">§ 167g.</num><heading> Promulgation of rules and regulations</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary is authorized to establish and promulgate such rules and regulations, as are consistent with the directions of this chapter and are necessary to carry out the provisions hereof.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idd0f75cd3-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e">(<ref href="/us/act/1925-03-03/ch426/s9">Mar. 3, 1925, ch. 426, § 9</ref>, as added <ref href="/us/pl/86/777/s2">Pub. L. 86–777, § 2</ref>, <date date="1960-09-13">Sept. 13, 1960</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/74/922">74 Stat. 922</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
